info.title: Account Opening Services
info.description: This catalog lists down all the account opening services.

parameters.name: x-req-id
parameters.description: The **x-req-id** field helps the server to log the request with the unique identifier. It is max **40 alphanumerics** but as of target system support, so it is mandatory that the value must be a non-repetitive number of at least 12 characters.

parameters.name: x-channel-id
parameters.description: The **x-channel-id** field helps the server to validate the request with unique channel source. **It is min 2 chars and max 6 chars** and all new channels are required to contact with the middleware team for their registration. i.e MB, CDC.

parameters.name: x-sub-channel-id
parameters.description: The **x-sub-channel-id** field helps the server to validate the request with unique channel source. **It is min 2 chars and max 6 chars** and all new channels are required to contact with the middleware team for their registration. i.e MB, CDC.

parameters.name: x-country-code
parameters.description: The **x-country-code** field is the country short code. **It is min 2 chars and max 3 chars** and in your case it will be 'PK'.

brokerId.description: Broker ID selected by client on bank portal, max numeric 5 characters

post.summary: This service will create an account against the provided CNIC number.
This service will generate customer CIF against the provided CNIC.
This service will push account data into core banking for final compliance.
This service is used to send data to core banking (in ZNA module) from web account opening portal.
This service will push customer CIF into core banking from web account opening portal.
The service will open an account (for agri) in core banking for an existing customer.
